Constructor injection beats field injection:

public UserController(UserRepository repository) {
  this.repository = repository;
}

Spring recommends it. Your tests will thank you.

Pagination without boilerplate:

@GetMapping + Pageable → Page<User>

?page=0&size=20&sort=name,asc — done.

code:
@GetMapping
public PagedResponse<User> getUsers(Pageable pageable) {
  Page<User> page = repository.findAll(pageable);
  return new PagedResponse<>(page.getContent(), ...);
}

@GetMapping("/api/users/{id}")
public String getUser(@PathVariable Long id) {
  if (id == 1) return "User found";
  throw new RuntimeException("Database connection failed!");
}

